tle>   How do guilds handle loot for people who like to play alts?</span><hr size=1> I'm surveying how guilds handle loot for people who play alts.  Use me as an example.  I regularly play a level 60 Warrior, 60 Shaman, and 58 Druid alternately (they're all on the same account).  I like Shaman the most, but my current goal is to get my Druid to level 60, so I play the Druid the most.<br>
<br>
My Warrior is always needed the most, so he's always online for the events and is labeled as my main.  My last two guilds wanted to get rid of /random in guild raids, so loot distribution was shaky.  Written loot rules prevented twinks from getting any loot (reason being that guilds can't afford the time to equip twinks if they want to grow to do new adventures).  Would anyone here consider my shaman or druid a twink?<br>
<br>
This was a partial reason why I left my last two guilds.  It didn't spark the move, but made me unhappy.  My Warrior became too well equipped (mainly from xp/single group winnings and trades, except my Edge of the NW, Champ's BP, and SS armor which I won with Amici) and the guild wasn't able to do anything that would interest him, so I wanted to play my other characters.  My Shaman and Druid don't rely on equipment much at all, but their epics would have helped a lot.  I had help from the guild with the harder parts of their epic, but was out on just about every drop (Warrior, Shaman, or Druid) for any item when I was able to play my Shaman or Druid.<br>
<br>
I think that the only system that makes it feel fair for me is the /random system and 3/4 of high level guilds are anti-/random in guild raids.<br>
<br>
Do any guilds have an unique way of handling this? <p><font size=2 face="Verdana, Arial">___________________________________<br>
