 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usolosstormreaper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solos Stormreaper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/Ring.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#778899>(11/5/01 12:07:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/Darkstar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How do guilds handle loot for people who like to play al</span><hr size=1> Random was suggested by me, since it's the simplest loot policy.  I agree that it makes extra downtime, but what loot policy doesn't?  It could be a 'holy' ritual for some (lower level) guilds where they stop everything to random and see the highest roller use (equip) his winnings and cheer and congratulate them.<br>
<br>
In a non-random guild, I good raid leader would probably already know the stats of every item that possibly drops and has a good idea of what everyone has.  They probably think of who to give what to before it drops as the raid starts, since they have to know who's there.  So, what if a quest armor piece like a Silk Wristband drops (probably one of the crappiest pieces).  It's crap, so who does the raid leader do with it?  It probably gets pretty close to rotting before something gets figured out (considering it's not a 55+ corpse, and the piece can't be MQed).  And what if that &quot;loot master&quot; isn't present?  Don't think anyone can manage that duty without a similar amount of experience.<br>
<br>
What about guests in a non-random guild?  Usually, they get screwed and get left with something like that Silk Bracer.  Leftovers, junk... You won't see many guests joining you.<br>
<br>
I think a guild based on /random (modified a little) can be just as good or better than any non-randoming guild, due to the big advantage of being able to pick up guests easily.   Amici is currently the only /random guild I know running, and I was thinking of a guild that was based on /random that could make it big and it turned out to be like Amici, sans a big alliance working with other guilds in order to kill dragons like Trak, Wuoshi, Sev, Talendor, and maybe make it into VP and do Velious uber mobs (Velk the Sorceror and Derakor level).<br>
<br>
I see a lot of new guilds popping up that aren't going in the direction I want.  They are just trying to recruit as many people as they can so they can do ToV by themselves.  I remember the days of having 5+ different guilds (Lost Souls, Order of the Wolf, Explorers of Norrath, Seekers of Lore, Unbroken...) allied together and doing Fear and Hate like the uber guilds like LoD were doing alone.  That was fun for me.<br>
<br>
<br>
I would apply for LoD, but if I did and was accepted, I would miss out on killing Trak for the first time, seeing Veeshan's Peak, killing all the Kunark dragons, the Chadok King and Queen, the named in SG, DN, WW, Velks, Kael, do my Druid epic, get my Coldain Ring.  Well, maybe I can if I made friends with a guild around that level to help out... <p><font size=2 face="Verdana, Arial">___________________________________<br>
